The paper discusses the use of neural networks for speech data, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. The paper specifically focuses on the comparison of RNN and FFNN architectures, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and analysis of performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of a priori knowledge, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of audio data, which could also suggest that it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
